verbose_text: There was a significant positive correlation (p < 0.0001, Pearson product-moment correlation) between corrected CSF angiogenin levels and corrected plasma angiogenin levels in controls, whereas in ALS patients (p = 0.21) the observed correlation was attenuated (XREF_FIG; r 2 control = 0.13, r 2 ALS = 0.011).
